Anthrax, Poland
---------------
Information received on [and dated] 8 Jul 2014 from Dr Krzysztof Jazdzewski, Deputy Chief Veterinary Officer, Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development, General Veterinary Inspectorate, Varsovie, Poland

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 18 Jun 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 07 Jul 2014
Report date: 08 Jul 2014
Date submitted to OIE: 08 Jul 2014
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 2001
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (basic), laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1: Pawlowka, Rachanie, tomaszowski (Tomaszow Lubelski), Lubelskie
Date of start of the outbreak: 18 Jun 2014
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Equidae / 7 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
